H0.text: Cardiac output is the volume of blood pumped by the heart in one minute, calculated by multiplying heart contractions by stroke volume.

H1.text: Liver output is the term calculated by multiplying heart contractions by stroke volume, meaning the volume of blood pumped by the heart in one minute.

H2.text: Respiratory output is the term calculated by multiplying heart contractions by stroke volume, meaning the volume of blood pumped by the heart in one minute.

H3.text: Blood output is the term calculated by multiplying heart contractions by stroke volume, meaning the volume of blood pumped by the heart in one minute.

A4.text: Cardiac output is calculated as the product of heart rate and stroke volume.
